CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 14, 1950, pg. 11, reads: "Visitor - Miss Irene Fuqua of Beckley, W. Va., spent the recent holiday week in Pittsburgh as the guest of Mr. and Mrs. Frank Lavelle of Clarissa Street. She also visited Mrs. Lavelle's mother, Mrs. Irene Gunn, in New Castle, Pa., later visiting friends in New York City. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Irene Fuqua seated in leaf patterned armchair with photograph of baby in background, possibly in home of Frank Lavelle, Clarissa Street, Upper Hill District
